"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here. I'm in Neadville, Texas at Messina Regenerative. Right over there are the rows that we've been uh using, and truthfully, Riley has been uh farming there for about two years now. It's a decent amount of space, but it's all we've been able to produce in terms of good humus. And the soil here is very bad. It's it's been overgrazed for many, many decades, and consequently, you can just take a look here. It's very compacted, it's mostly dust. If you try to stick your finger in here, there's nothing doing. Um it just is what happens when all the organic matter is used up out of the ground. And it's still a good uh little patch here, and there's still some good grasses growing, but not nearly what it could be. And a lot of the grasses that are growing are of a very particular type that respond to this compacted, dried out, uh, nutrient poor soil. And the idea is to get as much organic matter on this as we can because there's some horses in back that we could do some high amplitude grazing and kind of integrate this whole system together, but we're a little ways off because our compost is not going quickly. Uh, this is something where I'm trying to like find uh uh uh some capital to run this business a little bit because right now I'm the driver of and the pickup guy and I'm too old to do this. My back isn't good enough. I have to borrow my dad's truck twice a week. I do have the trailer, that's the one thing, but I would like to do more of this so that we can really take off here at Neadville or in Neadville at Messina Regenerative here. He's a market gardener as well, Riley, and he's just started uh market gardening for himself. He market gardened uh gardened for someone else uh for several years, but now he's doing it for himself, and I'm trying to follow in his footsteps. I have a much smaller uh footprint in terms of my garden, but I think my area is a little bit more fertile. Uh his composting is uh a little bit broader here. It's working out very well, but I have a much more active process. So I think I have a little bit more fertility and I'm adding a lot more of my compost into smaller beds. I have less space, more compost, so well not more compost, but uh quite a bit of compost. Not quite like nine barrels every two weeks like he's getting but uh anyway I just wanted to have a little talk about Neadville, Texas Messina Regenerative and what we're trying to do out here in growing or creating rich living soil so that we can produce living foods. Thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here.\",\n      \"start\": 0.56,\n      \"end\": 2.24,\n      \"duration\": 1.68,\n      \"confidence\": 0.984,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.978\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.36,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 1.36,\n          \"end\": 1.44,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.94\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Sc\",\n          \"start\": 1.6,\n          \"end\": 1.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.996\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ott\",\n          \"start